@end card

@dropdown "For developpers"

	@row
		@card
			In the [Marque](https://github.com/Loxed/marque) repository, the layouts are defined as `.css` files inside of `template/layouts/` and copied into each new project at `marque new <name>`. They directly apply onto the `index.html` inside of `template/themes/` when building the project. When creating new layouts, make sure you match the classes used in the `index.html` file.

			<!-- When creating a new project with `marque new <name>`, the `index.html` file is copied from `template/themes/index.html` and the layout `.css` files are copied from `template/layouts/`. This means that if you want to create a new layout, you need to create a new `.css` file in `template/layouts/` and then copy it into the new project when creating it. You also need to make sure that the new layout is applied in the `index.html` file of the new project. -->
		@end card

		@card
			```layout
			template/
			├── layouts/
			│   ├── sidebar.css
			│   └── topnav.css
			│
			└── themes/
				├── index.html
				├── index.js
				└── *.css
			```
		@end card
	@end row
@end dropdown